<br>
This would be quite true, except for one little problem. Monks become amazing tanks when they hit NToV+; where the high AC, high HP monk gear finally comes into effect. NOw, keeping this fact in mind, understand that for a monk to be at this level, his is most likely at least Baron or Brother (or the female semblance) and level 60. <br>
<br>
So, what does any of that mean you ask? Well, it's quite simple; at this level, monks have more than just good armor. They have T-staffs, Fungis, at least 36% haste, epic, and probably a pair of handwraps with at least 13/18 delay on each. <br>
<br>
So, what does ther equipment mean, you now ask. Well, monks are already amazing soloers at level 60. Don't believe me; the first class to solo Lodizal was a monk. Now, stick these NToV monks who, if they are iksars with fungi have about 32 hp/tick regen. Stick them in Velks, with their amazing damage output, 25% heal every 6 minutes, regen and feign death. Put them into Velks, or FG, or Seb, or KC or Chardok, put them with mobs that have low HP and what do you get? You get a class that can solo in these spots better and more effectively than just about any other class (they are #1 soloers in Velks). You get a person that can get more Xp from soloing than from virtually any group. <br>
<br>
Now, look at warriors. Yes, warriors can use Fungis and have NToV+ gear. However, they cannot even come close to matching a monk's damge output (hence why they can't keep agro off them). They do not have the monk epic. THey don't have the monk weapons, nor the ability to mend wound. Our clear lack of damage output and such healing forces us to rely on slow procs and buffs to solo far more than a monk. Our solo XP is nowhere near the XP we can get from say CT. <br>
<br>
<br>
Bottom line, we are forced to rely on groups for better XP. monks are not.  <p><center><p><font size = 3 colo = "blue"><b>Wilhelmm D'Averam<br>Warlord of the Apocalypse</b></font></p></center>

