<br>
The nerf reduced their mitigation only right?  Leaving avoidance alone and unchanged?  That's what I thought I had read.<br>
<br>
If I read that right, and that's what indeed is being changed, on top of test server reports saying they're taking the same DPS as before... I don't see this nerf changing anything at all.<br>
<br>
Monks at the end game were tanking non-defensive-requiring mobs better than warriors, and people complained about it.  Why did they tank better?  Because those level of mobs have an ATK rating so high that both the monk and warrior get hit for about the same amount of damage regardless of their AC values.  The monk, however, avoids more blows taken because of their superior avoidance side of AC.  This is why they took less damage... both get hit for about the same amount of damage when hit, but less hits are successfully landing on the monk.  Add in 125hp all/all low wieght items, and the monk makes an effective tank for those targets.<br>
<br>
But, the nerf changes mitigation, not avoidance.  So those end game monks should see absolutely no change in tanking effectiveness since the whole reason they were better at tanking those mobs in the first place was because of their superior avoidance (the part of their AC value that &quot;wasn't&quot; changed).  They didn't tank better because their mitigation was the same as a warrior's (the part of their AC value that &quot;was&quot; changed).  Their Avoidance made them better because of the circumstances.  Changing Mitigation isn't going to effect how well those monks tanked those big mobs... mitigation is a very small factor in how both warriors and monks take damage on such a mob.<br>
<br>
Those mobs are the same reason why warriors are opting for using Evasive over using Defensive on a lot of them.  It's better to not get hit in the first place as opposed to trying to mitigate a value that's near unmitigatable.  The ATK value is just too high to counter that way (mitigations wise that is).<br>
<br>
What I would have assumed would have happened, was that this nerf would have hurt the monks that are taking hits from more run of the mill mobs.  Standard exp mobs, solo/single-group hunting monks.  The mobs who's ATK is normal, and noticably mitigatable while taking hits from it.  But if test server results are saying that they're taking hits just the same, then the change is too small to even be noticed or worried about.  The nerf basically had no point as it basically did nothing (if what people are seeing from Test is true). <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=1402.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=1402.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=1402.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showMessageRange?topicID=1402.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showPrevMessage?topicID=1402.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showNextMessage?topicID=1402.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1402.topic&index=60><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.emailToFriend?topicID=1402.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.threadC